The paper deals with lower bounds on the security of one-time signature schemes constructed from random oracles, random permutations, and ideal ciphers. This falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficiency of signature schemes compared to symmetric primitives, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), computer engineering (cs.CE), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
